  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development and is described in the accompanying technical report, but the structured sensitivity analysis record has not been formally linked to this assurance package. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "High",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
